</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A756A095A34B218F136DC4376C6BB086" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="1EC7CED8D545B046823D002D9FE2410A" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B58A6840196FB64218683B79AE4D9965" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">
IUCN Red List Category: Endangered EN B1ab (i,ii,iii) + 2ab (i,ii,iii). B2: total area of occupancy less than 5000 km2 (ca. 799 km2). B1a, severely fragmented; B1b (i-iii), habitat continuing decline inferred. The suitable habitat for 
<taxonomicName id="685AE935B0DBD289CDD85C27D64FEBA0" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="feaniana">
<emphasis id="E69E200994790A8D3E42253B524469B5" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">Cyrtandra feaniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on Nuku Hiva (ca. 340 km2), Ua Huka (ca. 83 km2), Hiva Oa (ca. 315 km2), and Tahuata (ca. 61 km2) is restricted to mountain slopes and summits, indicated as an endangered environment that is threatened by human activity (deforestation and fire), feral animals, and invasive plants, reducing the extent of the forest (
<bibRefCitation id="19F9C883D7ED01F20FD1B98A3DEBDF95" author="Florence, J" journalOrPublisher="Allertonia" pageId="24" pageNumber="57" pagination="226 - 237" refId="B8" refString="Florence, J, Lorence, DH, 1997. Introduction to the flora and vegetation of the Marquesas Islands. Allertonia 7: 226 - 237" title="Introduction to the flora and vegetation of the Marquesas Islands." volume="7" year="1997">Florence and Lorence 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5F0FE3AE3AFC52D42484E822F7CDD540" author="Mueller-Dombois, D" journalOrPublisher="Springer, New York" pageId="24" pageNumber="57" pagination="444 - 460" refId="B14" refString="Mueller-Dombois, D, Fosberg, FR, 1998. Marquesas. Vegetation of the Tropical Pacific Islands. Springer, New York: 444 - 460" title="Marquesas. Vegetation of the Tropical Pacific Islands." year="1998">Mueller-Dombois and Fosberg 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="D99A35D959582B3EE3192134547578AB" author="Meyer, J-Y" editor="Gillespie, RG" journalOrPublisher="University of California Press, Berkeley" pageId="24" pageNumber="57" pagination="332 - 338" refId="B13" refString="Meyer, J-Y, Salvat, B, 2009. French Polynesia, Biology. In: Gillespie, RG, Clague, DA, Eds., Encyclopedia of Islands. University of California Press, Berkeley: 332 - 338" title="French Polynesia, Biology." volumeTitle="Encyclopedia of Islands." year="2009">Meyer and Salvat 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
